   Resources for the FCS

   FCA Handbook contains FCA Regulations, Statutes, FCA Board Policies,
   FCA Pending Regulations, Ethics Regulations, Bookletters and FCSIC
   Regulations.

   Legal Opinions contains summaries of selected legal opinions prepared
   by FCA's Office of General Counsel staff.

   FCA Examination Manual contains concepts, guidelines, and procedures
   used by FCA examiners for the examination of the FCS institutions.

   Informational Memorandums or Info Memos are FCA communications
   addressed to all Farm Credit institutions and are not meant to be a
   formalized category of communication.

   The Director's Role provides practical guidance and information about
   the duties, responsibilities, relationships, and liabilities of FCS
   institution directors.

   Loan Portfolio Management describes the major components of an
   effective loan portfolio management program.

